Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the helmet
The tire manufacturer Michelin, in cooperation with the Spanish Transport Safety Foundation (Fesvial), launched a campaign to promote helmet use, especially among the younger motorcycle drivers, as both companies announced today.
This initiative aims to draw attention to the importance of helmet use, as it is ultimately the only protective element that can prevent head injury or even death in the event of a motorcycle accident.
Michelin pointed out that this campaign was part of her commitment to road safety, which "contains more than just the design and manufacture of products that are becoming more and more secure every day" and also confirmed that they also contribute to the development of this objective by other actions of educational and informative character.
This new campaign to promote helmet use on the motorcycle, which runs under the slogan 'To be or not to be', will distribute posters at a first phase to over 500 motorcycle workshops in order to achieve the best possible distribution.
Finally, Michelin stressed that transport safety is "a constant concern" of the company, and precisely because as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, they are always committed to one of their main objectives being the development of ever safer products.
The sale of small trucks increases slightly again
After nearly two years, the car market for small transporters finally begins to see some light at the end of the dark tunnel.
The 9.425 vehicles registered in Spain in November represent an increase of 12.6% in 2008 and, more importantly, they are therefore the first increase even after 22 consecutive months with a steady decline, according to the figures presented by the manufacturer association Anfac and the car dealer association Ganvam.
However, these good figures are currently only to be enjoyed with great caution, as the reference data used for comparison are November 2008, which was a particularly bad year of sales with a 60 % decrease over the previous year.
