CNMV has also announced that this offer aims at the acquisition of 550.008 Federico Paternina shares at the price of EUR 7.65 per share, which in turn amounts to 8.95 % of the company's capital, consisting of EUR 6.142.786 in shares admitted to Madrid and Bilbao.
In addition, it has been announced that 5.592.778 million shares have been fixed, which cannot be transferred in any way until the completion of the tender and whose price has been fixed by Federico Paternina in accordance with the law.
New vehicle assessment programmes
