Estimated cost of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially in order to convince older professionals who are normally more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 small transporters and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with Internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for working hours, surcharges or discounts and then print out the cost estimate and pass it on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for assessing AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can pay without further delay.
Currently, the company Audatex is working to offer these images in three-dimensional formats.
This is an innovation that automechanics have been waiting for for a long time, as one can choose a door with it for example and then turn the image completely around to look at the inside.
